chunk_content: Many children with malnutrition are routinely identified through well S child clinics, when they have poor growth* (stunting, wasting, underweight / "falling off the T I growth curve") and/or a concerning mid-upper arm circumference (MUAC) measurement N (Refer to WHO Malnutrition Guidance for more information). All children identified with G growth problems should receive HIV testing and evaluation for TB with documentation under the respective MER indicator. While this service delivery modality may be part of either inpatient or outpatient services, if an individual could be reported under both malnutrition and another service delivery modality, report an individual only once and under malnutrition if the reason she/he/they were referred for HIV testing was due to growth problems.
